string demo-gui.__doc__
Initial value:
00001 '''
00002 Simple GUI (Graphical User Interface) to command an SDH. 
00003 
00004 A window based interactive application with GUI (Graphical User
00005 Interface) is started. It allows to command the SDH interactively
00006 with mouse and keyboard. The application uses the sdh.py python import
00007 library to connect to the SDH and the Tkinter package (Tk for python)
00008 to build the gui elements.
00009 If no RS232 port or CAN options to select the communication channel are
00010 given on the command line then an interactive window to select the 
00011 channel is shown first before the actual program is started.
00012 
00013 Apart from the intuitive gui elements the following keyboard shortcuts
00014 can be used:
00015 - <Pause/Break> : FastStop
00016 - <CTRL-c>      : Close application after powering off the controllers
00017 - <CTRL-C>      : Close application and keep controllers powered
00018 - <CTRL-m>      : Move axes of hand to the values set with the sliders
00019 - <CTRL-s>      : Stop movement of axes, but keep controllers enabled
00020 - <CTRL-a>      : Set Sliders to the current actual angle of the corresponding
00021                   axis
00022 - <CTRL-h>      : Set target position to "home" (all 0.0) Warning: collisions
00023                   are not checked!
00024 
00025 - Example usage:
00026   - Start interactive GUI. Before the actual interface appears a
00027     window will appear to interactively select the interface to use.
00028     > demo-gui.py
00029     
00030   - Start interactive GUI using an SDH connected via Ethernet.
00031     The SDH has IP-Address 192.168.1.42 and is attached to TCP port 23.
00032     (Requires at least SDH-firmware v0.0.3.1)
00033     > demo-gui.py --tcp=192.168.1.42
00034      
00035   - Start interactive GUI using an SDH connected to port 2 = COM3.
00036     (The port for the tactile sensors can be choosen interactively)
00037     > demo-gui.py -p 2
00038         
00039   - Get the version info of both the joint controllers and the tactile 
00040     sensor firmware from an SDH connected to 
00041     - port 2 = COM3 (joint controllers) and 
00042     - port 3 = COM4 (tactile sensor controller) 
00043     > demo-gui.py -p 2 --dsaport=3 -v                  
00044 '''
